reviews:
It is enjoyable for the hotel environment and the service.

The location close to Louvre is excellent which we could save lot of time for visiting all great spots in just 20 mins. Even we could walk to other places in just 30 mins.

With above, I would like to rate 5 points for it.

Very warm and welcoming staff. Top notch rooms and restaurant and very helpful concierge service. The hotel itself is vintage and impeccably preserved. Extremely clean. A very good location for visiting most top sites in Paris. I would highly recommend this hotel and would return again.

Hotel Regina is in a perfect location. We walked everywhere. We covered most parts of Paris. There is restaurants and shopping and sites nearby. The zoetrope is also close.
The hotel staff is wonderful. The concierge was very detailed oriented. The restaurant staff were friendly and outstanding.
Thank you for a lovely stay!

Our stay at the Hotel Regina Louvre was outstanding. From the first moment we arrived, we felt sincerely and warmly welcomed. Every member of hotel team was helpful, friendly, efficient, and professional. Our room was beautiful, unsurpassed for comfort and elegance. The in-room amenities were generous and much appreciated. Our entire experience was faultless. Breakfast was abundant and delicious, with excellent service. We especially appreciated the extraordinary help we received from the concierge team when we had to deal with a major travel disruption regarding our return flight. We look forward to returning to the Hotel Regina Louvre and hope it will be soon.

Enjoyed our 5-day stay at Hotel Regina. Best interaction was with "Chef Concierge" David who called to book a lunch reservation at a restaurant that showed being fully-booked online. He made a 5-minute phone call to the restaurant to get us a table.
Bellhop and doorman personnel were always rightly attentive. Ana (who speaks many languages) performed marvelously at check-in and welcoming tour. All front desk staff were always cheerful. Ideal location for visiting the Louvre and Musee d'Orsay. Had a great couple of drinks at the classy bar: Chateau-neuf-du-Pape served by the glass. The hotel is well decorated with much history in its walls.

Beautiful hotel with some of the friendliest staff I've ever encountered. I would most likely stay here again when I come back to Paris someday .
My one issue was that I needed to get back to the states and leave a day early. I'd already paid nearly $1000 US for for last night in France but your no refund policy made that impossible for me to just swallow and leave when I really needed to so it cost me a full day of production at my business.

The lobby of this hotel was lovely. It gave an excellent first impression. The hallway to our room seemed very sterile to us but I think that may be the look they were going for. The room was very nice. It was large and had everything we needed. The bed was comfortable. We looked out onto an alleyway and a rooftop so that was a bit disappointing. The location is great. We enjoyed going to the park that was adjacent to the hotel every day and it was nice being near the Louvre.

Breakfast was included in our room. They offered a decent buffet and we could also order eggs or pancakes. That took FOREVER. Even though there werent many people in the dining room our first morning, it took almost a half hour for an omelet. I learned to order my eggs as soon as I sat down following that. The dining room staff was very friendly.

The reason Im giving this hotel 4 stars is that we both felt that the staff behind the desk was very aloof. If we made a request or inquiry they were willing to assist but they certainly werent warm. After our experience in London where the staff tripped over themselves to be warm and welcoming, this was a bit disappointing. My husband feels the hotel deserves 3 stars but I did find that overall it was a nice hotel. That being said, I dont think we would stay there again

I attended with my wife and 23 year old daughter. The stay was wonderful. In order of highest accolades, the hotel was beautiful, the location was perfect, and the staff were wonderful. Concierge helped us on a daily basis and the recommendations for brunch and dinner places that fit our described needs was spot on. We had very high quality and high value dining experiences! We will come back to this hotel as a result of this visit!

Great Hotel great stay
The location in the heart of Paris
Rue Rivoli and the entrance to Luvre museum
metro, bus and many places to see by foot
The room we stayed - prestige room
spacious room
all facilities for great stay
coffee and tea corner was great
big bathroom big and comfortable bed
the staff of the hotel is professional and very friendly
We had breakfast which was good and healthy
defiantly we will come back

The Regina had no record of my guest profile on arrival. (I've been staying here 6 times a year for 10+ years.) so disappointing. What's the point of building loyalty if it is not acknowledged?
The hotel no longer subscribes to the BBC channels, a cut back that impact UK guests.
The hotel have changed the bed linen from smooth cotton to new, rough linen. Very unpleasant to sleep in.
Not good.
Please reinstate former Regina glory.

I stayed at Hotel Regina for two legs of my France trip. I was also traveling with my parents and brothers. So, we got to experience several rooms during our time there. All the rooms were uniquely decorated, but each was comfortable and quiet. The service was also great, but the location of Hotel Regina is the biggest plus - it really cannot be beat for a home base when visiting the sites of Paris!

The breakfast was exquisite, I highly recommend the mango macarons and omelets. The staff was extremely helpful and patient. In addition, the building was stunning and the location (right across the street from the Louvre) could not be beat.

The service was far better and more intimate than I ever imagined. Thank you for the bottle of champagne in my room! The doormen were very kind. Everyone knew my French was poor, so they greeted and spoke with me in English.

Our first trip to Paris for (too many!) years, and our first time at the beautiful Regina Louvre which we booked on the basis of location and the reviews we read.

We're so glad we chose to stay there-the hotel has an air of quality throughout, from the elegant reception area, the stylish decor and the comfortable room (we stayed in 312).

We had bed and breakfast-the breakfast is simple but better than most hotels in Paris, and the option of eggs on top of the buffet offering was good. The little bar is snug and serves a great variety of drinks and some decent snacks too.

Our room was good, and had a side view towards the Eiffel Tower. The room was really quiet and we slept comfortably every night.

We love to walk and this hotel is perfect for that. It's 5 minutes to the Louvre, and strolling through the Tuileries Gardens is great. It's was very easy to walk from here to the Arc Du Triomphe, from there to the Eiffel Tower and then "home" along the banks of the Seine.

So big thanks from us to all at the hotel-it's not cheap but it is worth the money, and we would certainly hope to return sooner rather than later!

The Hotel REGINA LOUVRE is ideally located about two blocks from the Louvre. I had a lovely view of the Eiffel Tower out of my room's window. The hotel staff is trained to perfection: all were friendly, hospitable, efficient, and knowledgeable. The hotel is the perfect size -- not huge, not tiny. The room was very comfy, with just the right pillows and bedlinens. Highly recommend for a Paris visit!

The Hotel Regina Louvre surpassed our expectations as soon as we were escorted through the beautiful door! We were a large group of five couples, most of which was our first time in Paris. We wanted to find something with some history, great location, and still 5 star. Hotel Regina definitely delivered. The service was impeccable! The ambiance was dreamy with its woodwork and velvet textures. I felt like I was in a movie the whole time. Its was very romantic at night in the tea room with delicious champagne and views of the Eiffle Tower sparkling. The clock looked like Cogsworth from Beauty and the Beast. The lighting! Ahhh just magical!

We reserved a prestige room and were pleasantly surprised by the size. Everyone warned us about Frances hotel rooms being small. This room was a great size with a view of the Eiffle tower. The room was beautiful, clean, smelled nice, and was kept that way by the wonderful housekeeping staff. Fresh waters at turn down and a perfectly cleaned room. I think I even slept till 1pm one day, it was so comfortable!

The bar staff was outstanding! They made a perfect Old Fashioned for my husband and kept my champagne glass full. I also was given great advice on some new red wines to try. I even bought a few bottles once I got home. The staff is well trained and knowledgeable. They also always found seating for the 10 of us. We felt so welcomed and taken care of.

The breakfast was delish and the restaurant ran smoothly. We were most always rushed in the morning trying to grab breakfast before our packed days and the staff was always accommodating, quick with our orders, and even helped with to-go orders.

If you, like us, are new to Paris then please make sure to email the concierge. I was nervous to book activities since I do not speak French. I heavily leaned on the hotel concierge Mickael to help us plan our activities. Mickael and his team made our trip be the dreamy unforgettable experience that will keep us coming back to Paris and Hotel Regina. He booked our group for a private tour of the Louvre, a VIP champagne show at Crazy Horse, and a magical luxury boat tour. All of these went seamlessly and booking through the hotel took away any nerves I had. They were so professional on email and in person.

And last but not least, Slah, who helped my husband and I to our room, was fantastic! He was wonderful and professional and made us feel like the most important customers at the hotel.

We were beyond happy with our time at Hotel Regina. It just wasnt long enough. We will be back soon!

This was the 8th stay at this hotel - it was even more exceptional than ever. It is in an excellent location, within walking distance to almost all attractions, and with close access to various bus stops and metro stations. Our room was an Eiffel Tower Junior Suite with a magnificent view of the Tuileries and the Louvre, the Eiffel Tower, Les Invalides, Musee d'Orsay, Arc de Triomphe, Rue de Rivoli, Place des Pyramides...it can't get better than this. The service is absolutely excellent, the staff are all so polite and obliging. Breakfast is really good, especially the eggs made to order. Breakfast staff are extremely efficient, they take so much care of patrons. The rooms are impeccable, kept clean and fresh, lovely toiletries, bed linen and towels, always complimentary water available. It feels great to return to the hotel after a tiring albeit enjoyable day out, and finding a neat room, curtains tied back, crisp bed linen, fresh towels, supreme cleanliness. It feels also welcoming and comforting to return after a late dinner and find the room refreshed for the night, used towels replaced, bed made up neatly, curtains drawn for privacy. The household staff, both morning and evening, are definitely commendable.
The front desk staff and doormen are fantastic! Simply cannot be nicer or more efficient.
One last thing, we're already booked for our usual Easter break at Regina, our 9th stay - I think that makes our satisfaction with this hotel absolutely clear!

Your classic French style hotel. Great service , rooms are spacious and quite nice , hotel itself gives a really old french feel which was great , and the views were the best part! Amazing views of the Eiffel Tower, the Arch and all of Paris. Overall would reccmoned but only got to stay 1 night so would go back for longer next time.

We were absolutely overjoyed with Hotel Regina! The accommodations and the location are absolutely perfect. We had a junior Eiffel Tower suite and it was phenomenal! Our Every need was taken care of and the staff is so accommodating. I really dont want to say anything negative about this hotel at all because it is one of the best we have ever stayed at, but the beds were very hard. For people who love sleeping on a hard mattress, it will be to your delight, but just a little bit too hard for us. Dont let that stop you, youll love every single thing about the Hotel Regina! Well be back!

We traveled with children and the family suite was perfect with a separate room with bunk beds. The unobstructed view of the Eiffel Tower was an unexpected bonus. The hotel as a whole is in an excellent location and the service was impeccable with a concierge that was extremely helpful and meticulous in the managing of logistics (transfers, etc). .

I have never understood the idea shared amongst Americans that the French are rude. I have never experienced this in my five trips to France. This trip has been no different. In fact, my stay at the Hotel Regina was overly accommodating. The staff at this hotel went out of their way to make our stay relaxing and smooth. In fact, my wife had a bacterial sinus infection during our stay, and the staff helped us arrange an on site physician visit. This was a significant help! This saved my wifes trip. The front staff constantly asked me if she was feeling better when I walked by the desk. The room service was phenomenal and the restaurant on site was one of the best in the area! I highly recommend the stay at this hotel. The hotel is a bit older and has been preserved with the renovations and the furniture. The hotel is quite charming!

We had a fabulous stay at the Regina Louvre this past week. The family room was perfect for our family of four with two teen boys. The hotel is located in a central place making it easy to get to all the main Paris attractions. The hotel itself is gorgeous! The staff is also so wonderful and attentive. Denis, at the restaurant always made sure to take good care of us and even went above and beyond to pack us take away boxes when we missed breakfast. Audrey got us last second dinner reservations at a fabulous restaurant. Everyone was lovely even though we spoke very little French. We will definitely be staying there again.

Our family had an absolutely wonderful stay at Hotel Regina. It was our first time visiting Paris and I must emphasize that the location is perfect if you plan on visiting the tourist attractions. It is walking distance from major sites including the Louvre, Tuileries Garden, Musee D'Orsay, Muse de l'Orangerie, and the Arc de Triomphe, as well as the Seine River. For shopping enthusiasts, it is a short walk to Rue Saint-Honor.

We particularly chose a room with the view of the Eiffel Tower. If it is available, I would recommend this option. Before going to sleep, we would always count down the seconds until the Eiffel Tower would light up (tip: for the first five minutes of every hour after sunset up until midnight). The king bed was incredibly comfortable and service was great. We were welcomed with water and chocolates (really good, you must try it)!

We could not have chosen a better hotel as a base for a few days of sightseeing in Paris. Not too big, very smart and with the mostly friendly and helpful front of house staff we have ever experienced. Nothing was too much trouble for them to arrange for us. Hotel location was just right - relatively quiet and relaxed, with lovely gardens opposite and The Louvre less than a 5 minute walk away. Would recommend to anyone.

My wife and I went in to check the hotel out but the first staff member we encountered identified us as curious tourists and discouraged us from looking around. This is not smart for a hotel which relies on tourists. We were not dressed like rock stars but neither did we look like low budget travellers. So we will not darken their door again. Maybe that suits them just fine. Every other high end hotel we have looked around has been very welcoming.

The staff of the hotel were extremely accommodating and helpful. The staff at the restaurant, the concierge, the front desk, etc. The rooms were very comfortable and the location next to the Louvre is unbeatable! The breakfast was a delightful spread of French food. Would definitely stay here again and recommend to friends!

I had the most wonderful stay Hotel Regina. The service was fantastic, the room was gorgeous and the interior/lobby/restaurant were all absolutely perfect. The gym, sauna and steam room were all really nice additions. I cannot recommend this hotel enough - the location was amazing and I will definitely be back!

Very charming hotel. Awesome experiences with comfort and all servise. Tasty breakfast. Beautiful view. Perfect location in center next to the Louvre museum and 40 minutes walk to the Eiffel Tower. Merci beaucoup

Beautiful hotel, great location, close to Metro line 1 which gets you anywhere. Restaurants close by. Safe area to walk around. The staff was amazing, very helpful, friendly and welcoming. The room was large, clean and comfortable. I will stay here again if ever back in Paris

I first stayed at The Regina in the summer of 2019 and loved it so that I came back in the winter of 2023 but the experience was a bit different
ProsThe location is the BEST, reception desk were friendly and warm, beautiful suites with Eiffel tower views. The room is lovely ,housekeeping is great, food at breakfast and food at afternoon tea were good, the bar is beautiful, the service at breakfast is great.
Consthe concierge desk is extremely cold and unfriendly and seems generally uninterested in the guests - lacking even a good morning or good evening when passing by. The Wi-Fi is fair because it is an old hotel (although they did try to help by providing a booster. The breakfast room gets louder as the weekend approaches with some children watching loud videos on IPads (hotel may want to suggest headphones so other guests are not bothered). The afternoon tea was the same with grown men watching sports loudly on phones in the lobby (why does hotel look the other way).

Truly excellent, absolutely French experience. All staff top notch! The decor is beautiful; the room was comfortable and totally quiet, in the middle of the 1st arr. It was a lovely, warm environment that made being in Paris really perfect! Merci!

Having spent two nights at the Regina Louvre, our overall experience was exceptional. The staff went above and beyond to accommodate all our requests - we even had the chance to check-in in our native language, Portuguese. The icing on the cake was our 4th-floor suite, where a glorious Eiffel Tower view awaited. Location-wise, this is a great area for those wishing to cover some of Paris's most famous attractions, namely The Louvre, which is just across the street. I plan on returning!

It's a five-star hotel worthy of its rating classification, it's really that simple. The professionalism of the employees is humbling, the room is perfectly clean, the breakfast is great and everything's pretty much perfect.
we went for a long weekend for my wife's birthday and couldn't have asked for a better experience, the service was great and the location excellent. All the staff were extremely helpful and friendly

Excellent hotel with refined presentation and professional staff. We stayed for 12 days and despite the bitterly cold outside, the return after a busy day was always welcomed by the hotel's warmth and staff. The Reception staff generated bistro ideas on a daily basis, reserved the table and made our lives easier in an environment which can be quite demanding. Our compliments to the Reception Desk, most explicitly to Ms Audrey who encapsulted top notch efficiency with grace and charm.

The GREAT: I loved that it was a stone's throw away from the Louvre and the Tuileries garden so it made for nice morning or early evening strolls. All the major tourist areas and shopping (along Rue St. Honore) were within a short walking distance. There were so many restaurants nearby as well but if you are too tired to venture out, the hotel dining was great. I had the daily breakfast (i don't know if this was an add on) but it was good to have especially for early risers with a good variety. I tried the room service food the first day and i enjoyed it.

The OK: The room and the bathroom were on the small side and quite average but still comfortable. It had the usual amenities but wasn't exactly luxurious. I like that it was never noisy despite its location.

For me, what made this hotel feel really luxurious was the excellent staff. I felt very pampered and welcomed here. Sometimes when the hotel is a little more upscale, the service becomes too cold and stuffy but I never felt that here. All in all, a memorable stay. Well worth its price.

What a historic and beautiful hotel. I very much appreciate the preservation of the hotel with so many details such as the wood carved structure over the front entrance . You feel the glamour and it says a lot about the fact that it was preserved. Too many are renovating all this gorgeous hand carved artwork for modern looks. The lounge room is very inviting and you cant wait to cozy up in a corner after a day walking all over Paris. We were welcomed very nicely by the bellman as we arrived followed by the gentleman at the reception clerk. The rooms are gorgeous and elegant and the view is like no other. Not to mention the location of the property is simply TOP! We were there as a family ok holiday and we all loved it. The team does an excellent job from entry to exit. Well done!

This was our second visit to the Hotel Regina Louvre - and it was even better than our first experience. The hotel is gorgeous - historic and modern at the same time. Tremendous service by our Housekeeper (Fanny), the front desk receptionist (Sophie), and the concierge (Mehdi-Pierre). The restaurant, esp at breakfast, was superb in terms of food and service. The bell-staff - tremendous. Grand merci for a fantastic time. See you next year!

We recently booked an extended stay and could not have been happier with this hotel. The staff were gracious and helpful. Our room was large, and the bathroom had a tub and a separate shower. Everything was tastefully decorated, and the Christmas decorations were exquisite. So please at the location, central to what we wanted. We would stay here again and highly recommend it.

The hotel is beautiful and tastefully decorated.
The room was pretty and big with large, nice bathroom. The location is ideal to walk out and shop and eat. It goes on forever with choices. Staffs are extremely nice and helpful. Not just one of my favorite hotels in Paris, one of my favorite places on the planet.

We booked a suite that over looked the Eiffel Tower and park area. Our room was large, clean and comfortable. Our room was on the corner and it was extremely quiet. We never heard any traffic! The bathroom could have used an update (it was clean and very adequate..don't let this be a reason to not stay here.) The staff was kind and helpful. Location is perfect and easy to walk anywhere!

Run down and tired hotel. The only thing they have going for themselves is a fantastic location. That is really spectacular for Paris as you are a stone throw away from many tourists attractions. I cannot wrap my head around how can one award 5 stars to this hotel. Stuffy rooms worth Soviet design from 70s. The shower room was particularly ugly. The only nice thing in my room was a view of Eiffel tower. Whole hotel smells a bit weird. Service is poor, and they couldnt get their printer to work to print the bill. Also, they were incapable of ordering the cab.

We continue to return to the Regina.... for everything it offers. An historic palace property with such a gorgeous entrance and lobby.... consider the special suites with the special views to enhance your stay -- especially if you're only in Paris occasionally. Rates for those special rooms so reasonable compared to other Palace hotels in Paris -- which are no shockingly expensive.

I had the opportunity to make a stopover in Paris before heading to another part of France for business. My wife was able to join me for this quick Paris adventure. I apologize in advance as I didn't catch anyone's name. When we arrived the reception, the woman checking us in was amazing, she was outgoing, pleasant and told us all about the hotel and escorted us to the rooms. The bellman delivered our suitcases and explained a little more about the room. The concierge was great the woman in the midday and the gentleman at night.

My favorite person was the head waiter/Maitre'd (gentleman with bald head). He was inviting, professional, funny and provided the most luxury service you can ask of someone. Even when a tray of glasses crashed to the floor, he never raised his voice or had a bad interaction with the staff. They calmly cleaned up the mess and resumed excellent service. The food at the hotel is amazing! I had the Caesar salad and the Rossitto for dinner, and it was one of my best meals in Paris. Then before we left for the airport, we had a France IPA (delish) and split a burger and Caesar again. So good! The hotel is also in perfect location for the metro and sightseeing. Looking forward to the next time we are in Paris. Thank you for making my first time there memorable.

The best location, best experience and best views of Louvre, Eifel and the Gardens.
We got upgrades to the most amazing room for our 20th anniversary.
Staff was the most helpful that after 3 days we felt like family :-)

We are already planning our next year visit to this hotel!

This hotel is wonderful. We reserved a jr. suite with an Eiffel Tower view and the first room was not acceptable b/c the bathroom door swung into you at the sink; bad design. They moved us in a few days and our next room was beyond wonderful! Everyone at the hotel is more than happy to help in any way. They are courteous and friendly and can't do enough for you, even giving us a take-out breakfast on a morning when we had an early tour. There were 2 couples on this trip and we all loved the bar after we got back from evenings out, and had a very nice dinner our last night at the hotel. Breakfast was amazing and you could get eggs any way you wanted along with the huge buffet of fruits, cold cuts, cereals, yogurts, smoked salmon, etc. I would love to go back to this hotel if I ever return to Paris. Perfect location and beautiful old world style. I can't say enough good things about it.

The hotel is perfectly located, provides an old world charm, has an excellent staff that is incredibly friendly/attentive and is also a great value for such a beautiful interior and exterior setting. We are looking forward to a return visit soon. Thank you to the staff for making this such a memorable part of our trip to Paris!

This is one of the best hotels we have ever stayed on. The service was top notch and the hotel was beautiful. It is beautiful hotel. We stayed in a king size bed room (hard to find in Paris) and the room size was great. The service and location were the best parts of the hotel. Michael, the concierge, and the rest of the front desk staff were incredible. Michael's dinner suggestions were absolutely excellent. They arranged for our tickets to the Versailles Palace and taxis when needed. If you visit Paris, you cannot find a more convenient location. Walked to all the shopping districts, Eiffel Tower, train stations and it is across the street from the Louvre. We are coming back to Paris and we'll be staying here for sure.

Beautiful room and hotel. Unequivocally Parisisan! Will come back next year and stay!
I've seen negative reviews on here stating that this hotel is run down...it's NOT rundown, it's an old building. Take it for what it is. It's beautiful, the location is perfect and the staff is great. It's Paris! If you don't want a true Parisian experience in an old hotel , go stay at the Hilton. Will bring my family next year. My parents have stayed here numerous times and it is worth it! Thank you Hotel Regina Louvre for such a magical stay. Prices are competitve as well.

We stayed at the Regina and we will be back as soon as possible. We had a beautiful family room with 2 adults and 2 children. The concierge was phenomenal with recommended bookings. Central to all we wanted to do in Paris. The perfect stay.

We are a family of 5 - the family suite was perfect and the hotel was friendly and very responsive.
Perfectly located next to the Louvre and with a real family feel.
A beautiful building but well looked after and modernised.
A fantastic stay - I would highly recommend.

My Husband and I recently celebrated our 40th wedding anniversary at the wonderful Hotel Regina Louvre. We were treated special from the moment we walked into the lobby. The staff was genuinely happy to spend time explaining the amenities.
We were surprised with rose petals on the bed and Champagne chilled on ice that evening. The hotel is walking distance to the Louvre, The Seine River and is perfectly located in the historic district. We were able to walk easily and take evening strolls looking at the Eiffel Tower twinkling in the evening.! The rooms are updated and very comfortable . It was such an amazing week. We can't wait to come back on another special occasion. Thanks Audrey, Morgan for all your help with requests. We really appreciate all the special attention and everyones smiles!

This hotel was very charming with excellent fixtures.

If you are looking for a quintessential Parisian hotel in the middle of everything, this is it.

I deeply appreciated the elegance of the hotel and the friendly front desk team.

The gym was small, but functional.

The two downsides were that the sheets were very scratchy and uncomfortable, and housekeeping wasnt as impeccable as it could have been. Otherwise, I would recommend this hotel.

Staff was always attentive and the hotel is beautiful. The hotel is a nearly all American clientele. The hotels location is perfect if you are wanting a very central location within the fashionable district. The rooms were very spacious with attentive amenities.

Centrally located to many attractions and shopping, this 5 star hotel has it all - amazing staff, beautiful rooms, and great breakfast! The hotel is literally across the street from the Louvre and Jardin de Tuileries. Over the bridge across the Seine river is the Musee d'Orsay and the historic Saint Germain area. The Palais Royale area was only 3 blocks away and the Vendome plaza was 3 blocks in the other direction. The Royal Opera House was about 5 blocks away. Also close to Galleria Lafayette for great shopping! We walked everywhere! We cannot say enough great things about Hotel Regina!

Beautiful hotel. Very well appointed. We stayed in Junior Eiffel Tower Suite, a large room with large bathroom (including deep bath with shower over, plus double basin) and of course views of Jardin des Tuilleries and over to the Eiffel Tower. Service generally is impeccable, with some missteps, including housekeeping leaving dirty cleaning cloths in the room, one of the staff (who I'm guessing was a junior food manager) forgetting our orders, twice even after he specifically asked if we would like something to eat.

Like a lot of hotels, I suspect Regina is trying to recoup lost revenue following Covid, as there were some very noticable cost cutting which wouldn't be expected at a top end hotel, including one small soap in the bathroom (yes there is shower gel on the wall in a reusable bottle), two bottles of water provided (on day one only, no replenishment), a number of the English TV channels had not been subscribed to so really only the basis news channels, only two sachets of instant coffee (and two small milk serves) per day with a note saying if further coffee is required, it can be provided at the menu rate (which would be 7 each plus service fee). To put that into perspective, we are paying (yes, we are still here) 1000 a night for the room.

Quite a few of the staff are obviously fairly new (one has been in Paris three months, another told us they'd been here 'a short while') which may explain some of the staff missteps, but not the cost cutting.

The location is very good, with walking distance to most key points in the city.

Would we stay here again? Perhaps but would be hesitant given the cost cutting to improve profits.

Everything was first class. The food, drinks, and accommodations were excellent. Being a Margarita drinker, the Bar made me a good one. They also prepared cosmopolitans and old fashions which we had not been able to find else in France.
A big breakfast was a great way to start the next morning.
And fortunately we got a room with a wonderful view of the Eiffel Tour

We had a wonderful experience at the Hotel Regina Louvre. The hotel accommodated our large family, and my dream of a suite overlooking le Tour Eiffel and Jardin de Tuileries came true. The staff is absolutely phenomenal.

We were able to walk to many restaurants and sites with no issue--about twenty minutes' walk to the Champs-Elysees, five minutes to Louvre.

Hurricane Ian cancelled our flights, and the staff at the Regina made sure we had accommodations--they moved our stuff for us and even surprised us with a special view for our extra nights.

The hotel is old (120 ans!) but renovated nicely. Highly recommend!

I had booked a room here prior to Covid specifically to see the last day of the Tour de France in Paris. The pandemic and various circumstances prevented our trip for 3 years, yet Reservations Manager, Mrs. Fanny Stehly, corresponded with me throughout those entire 3 years, making sure that my dream of experiencing the Tour de France up close and personal came true. I know of no other hotel who has that level of guest support; Mrs. Stehly well represents the attitude of this hotel - professional, helpful, and very personable. The rooms were spacious and elegant, but still cozy and relaxing.

Very good service and welcoming staff. Room was lovely and very clean. Room service restaurant was able to accommodate my allergies. Enjoyed being so close to Jardin de Tuileries and walked there every evening after dinner. Easy to access the left bank and metro. Except for speeding bicycles in the pedestrian crosswalks, a superb location for Louvre, Muse d'Orsay and wandering both banks of the Seine. This trip was to replace ones booked for 9/2020 and 9/2021 which I cancelled due to Covid. After losing a lot of money to a Paris apartment rental agency, I chose a hotel and will always do so in the future. Paying the higher flexible rate in case of another emergency was worth it to me knowing I would only lose one night's stay if another coronavirus variant or border shutdown happened. Staying at Hotel Regina Louvre was a wonderful treat!

We recently had the pleasure of staying at the hotel Regina with a group of 9 people. (5 adults and 4 children). The concierge was extremely attentive and always willing to help arrange every little detail we needed. The lobby, bar and restaurant were absolutely beautiful and the recommended tour guides set go for each day were fantastic! Especially Victoria, seraphine and helga! All absolutely knowledgeable and wonderful! The location is central and walkable to most popular places! We will definitely be retuning!

Junior Suite with Eiffel Tower view was fantastic. Lots of space and a great view of the Eiffel Tower, Gardens, and the Louvre. Service at hotel was great - everyone was very friendly and helpful. Got a recommendation or 2 from the concierge, both good.

The staff was very welcoming and knowledgeable. We do not speak French, but it was very easy to communicate and understand each other in English.
Their recommendations for restaurants, shops, etc. was exactly what we needed.
Everyone was very Friendly.

Very nice.
First visit in room 410 was excellent.
Second visit in room 309, not so great.
The view was wonderful in both.
The water on my bathroom floor in Room 309 was disconcerting because it was not addressed in a timely manner.
The clean up, lack of water, and attention to detail in room 309 was not up to your standard. Disappointing.

The breakfasts were lovely, and the service impeccable.
The drinks in the lounge were a bit slow in coming but ok.
I ate dinner in the bar/loungeit was very good.

The staff was very helpful and made one feel at home.
Thank you!

My wife and daughter went to Paris and stayed at Hotel Regina Louvre for my daughters 18 birthday gift. She wanted me to write this review because I picked this hotel because she didnt want to do it , she found it amazingly clean and in a perfect location. The staff she said were ladies and gentlemen who couldnt do enough for them . She had the junior Eiffel Tower suite room 515 and said the view was perfect, its a corner suite so from one balcony you are facing the louvre and the other balcony you face the Eiffel Tower. There is a beautiful park across the street almost like a botanical gardens. She said the cab service was fantastic the doormen saw to that. This hotel she said is her go to when in Paris. Now the reason I chose this hotel after a week of searching on sites like Expedia, Booking.com and trip advisor where there are thousands of hotels and reviews is because of the excellent reviews but also the fact that its next to the louvre which has billions of dollars in art in it and a ton of security in and around it you may not see them but their there . It has to be one of the safest places in Paris. Anyway thank you to the entire staff at Hotel Regina Louvre for making the two loves of my life feel special, if theres anything I can do for you please contact me

The Regina is a beautiful hotel that has a touch of art deco and old world luxury. Our room provided all the storage, and comfort needed, the view of the Eiffel Tower at night was amazing. The courtyard provides a quiet place while being served, Although the courtyard is serene I would not want that to be my only view. Service was exceptional, and immediate. Slah Fares, manager, personally took charge of having the twin beds separated for my friend and I. He was gracious and understanding, it was obvious he had our best interest in mind. We were able to walk to the Louvre, and other sites. It's truly a wonderful hotel.

First of all I can not say enough about how fantastic our stay was at the Regina Hotel. We stayed four nights, five days and from the moment we first entered the lobby, we were met with kind, exceptional service especially after a long day of travel with a 15year old and 12year old. I wish I had the name of the young woman who checked us in as my daughter was not feeling well after getting car sick as she could not have been more helpful and kind (checked in on July 13th so if that helps she should definitely get a raise :)). They allowed us to check in early which we were so grateful for. The room was beautiful and clean as we checked into a junior suite with beautiful big windows that opened to the courtyard. The concierge team was incredible helping us make reservations for restaurants along with recommendations on how to get places. They truly were amazing, kind, and helpful. The restaurant and bar was also great with wonderful staff. I truly hope to return to the Regina Hotel as it was truly an amazing experience. I normally do not write reviews however our experience at this hotel went above and beyond my expectation.

As most of you who follow my reviews know I am extremely honest about my reviews. My reviews are never meant to be vindictive, but true and honest for the next guest to follow. This hotel is Amazing.. commencing with the front desk staff, doorman,housekeeping including the bar stafflocation and service all Five stars.. The Praise first start with leadership like Beligh Bouddha at the front desk, as the assistant manage he sincerely goes above and beyond to ensure your stay is commenced with genuine and sincere care for the guest. The rooms are well appointed -large for Paris and renovated .. and - yes air conditioned!!! The breakfast is lavish in an elegant restaurant or try the wonderful room service. The Bar area for cocktails is wonderful and very well staff and serviced. The decor is classic Parisian with every attention to detail. And of course the location is ideal.. walking distance to the Louvre, Notre dame, Tower Eiffel.. with wonderful cafes and the tulillerie gardens surrounding. In summary ..truly a wonderful hotel with superb service and staff!!! Enjoy Dr Neil Persaud

This hotel represents the best of Paris. Elegance, charm, fabulous location, highly competent and caring staff - we could go on and on. My mother and I each had separate rooms for nine nights and it was a truly lovely experience. Kudos to Denis in the dining room and his breakfast colleague (I sadly did not learn her name) who was so kind and charming and she has the perfect personality for the hospitality industry - the Hotel Regina is lucky to have her. The bar, restaurant, concierge, front desk, maid service - all wonderful. And the rooms are so quiet! We could find no fault in any aspect of our heavenly stay. Highly recommended and we will return with great joy to do so.

Looking for a friendly welcome? A hotel with helpful staff? Great wifi? A home away from home? Then don't consider this hotel! The location is fantastic for several major sites in the city (Louvre...), but the level of service at the reception and in the restaurant as well as the friendliness and attitude of the staff are not at all at the 5 star level. A big disappointment in this regard. We won't be back

Wonderful stay at the Hotel Regina! Beautiful accommodations and excellent service! Location is perfect! The Concierge group go out of their way to make your stay incredibleanything you want they do their best to make it happen!

Beautiful hotel. Excellent service. Prestige Suite had plenty of room for two adults and two elementary-aged children. Room service was particularly fabulous for taking some quiet time in the middle of long, wonderfully packed, but hot days. It was 90-98 during our visit and the AC was perfect. Thoroughly recommend.

Just a wonderful place. Great accommodations, great staff. The location is ideal, just steps from the Louvre. We especially enjoyed our daily breakfasts, which were very French, but a Lao able to accommodate our American tastes. We will certainly return.

Our room had four balconies all overlooking the Eiffel tower. We traveled with our girls and the location could not have been more perfect. Proximity to museums, shopping and dining was fabulous. Concierge was beyond helpful and we will definitely be back!

I was supposed to visit for my anniversary two years ago but covid delayed those plans. I finally got to visit this year and I was prepared to lower my expectations somewhat after reading about the changes at so many other hotels because of the effects of the last two years on businesses. I am THRILLED to be able to say that Hotel Regina did not require that of me. They lived up to ALL my expectations and Im so glad I chose Hotel Regina Louvre for our anniversary visit to Paris. Its a lovely and charming hotel with a classic and elegant style. It combined an interesting history and a certain Belle Epoque style with modern touches (soundproofing!) and a wonderful location that was incredibly convenient to so many sights. The room itself was very comfortable but the Eiffel Tower view really made for what will be a great memory.

But I really have to compliment the staff because the service is what made the stay extra special. Everyone, and I do mean EVERYONE, who works there puts in the extra effort that defines the best in "hospitality", from the people working in the bar and restaurant to the reservation team and even housekeeping. They made me feel like a "Regina." "Warm, friendly and efficient" does not do them enough justice. This is a topnotch staff. They all went above and beyond. The Concierge team was working for me EVEN BEFORE we arrived, always responding quickly with answers to my questions and providing information and helping me to arrange things. I could not have been happier with the wonderful service and help I received from everyone.

If you are looking for a wonderful place to stay when you're in Paris look no further because you found it. I would gladly visit again.

This hotel is truly a gem. Historic but renovated, in an absolutely wonderful location (close to the Louvre, across the street from the Tuileries Gardens and walking distance to so many places including the Vendome shopping area, the Marais, the Opera, Galeries Lafayette, The Orsay, etc.). My daughter and I stayed here on a mother daughter trip and booked the Eiffel Tower suite. The room (actually two rooms) was very large with two bathrooms (from my understanding there is only one suite that has two bathrooms and in ours one bathroom was more modern and the other seemed older and not very renovated) and the most beautiful view of the Eiffel Tower and Gardens. It was such a treat to watch the sparkling lights at night from our balconies. The room was classically decorated and elegant without being over the top. The service at the hotel was generally very good with mostly nice and helpful concierges and very nice reception staff. We were sad to leave but hope to return and we wouldnt consider staying anywhere but this hotel on our next trip to Paris!

We had a lovely stay in Paris at Regina! The rooms are beautiful and the staff are excellent! They surprised my daughter with a delicious bottle of wine and yummy cookies! The location is fabulous! I would stay here again! The beds were great!

We stayed in the family suite with our two elementary aged children. The second bedroom and full bathroom were a true luxury in Europe. The concierge was extremely attentive both before and during our stay. The location across from the Louvre and the Gardens was convenient for children needing to run off some energy. The central location made it easy to travel across the city. We will definitely return to this hotel for future trips to Paris.

Our Stay was simply wonderful !!! Thank you Valentino, the GM and the excellent Regina Staff. The breakfast buffet is copious and delicious !!! Thank you Giselle for greeting us each day with a smile :)
We really appreciated the personal attention to our Birthday Celebration in Paris. The Hotel is perfectly located just adjacent to The Louvre Museum, near transportation and walking distance to most monuments in central Paris. The room is classic French Elegance and the staff is wonderful. We really appreciated the Eiffel tower view !!! Perfectly located, beautifully appointed, also the best value in Paris for 5 Star Hotels !!!!
I would definitely recommend this hotel.
Thank you ,
Eric

We had a great stay at this hotel! We arrived there for our first stop on our honeymoon and they made sure that we felt special. They placed champagne in our room and were so kind/friendly. I cant recall the receptionists name but he definitely went out of his to take care of us on multiple occasions. It was also nice that they recognized us every single time we passed by even though there were so many others staying at the hotel. The concierge booked reservations for dinner for us multiple nights and picked amazing spots for us to go eat. We are very thankful for the hospitality.

A very well-run hotel. Excellent breakfast and concierge services. Staff have a good command of English. It is an oasis of calm and serenity compared to the crowds outside. The location is excellent and there is a taxi stand outside. It was a breeze to get to the Louvre. It is minutes away from the Tuileries metro station that connects to the major sights in Paris. You can enjoy early morning walks in the Tuileries garden with views of the Eiffel Tower before the crowds.

Beautiful art nouveau hotel,old fashion Parisian style. Class. Top location,quiet, good quality breakfast and dinners,descreet,very nice stuff,great,atmospheric bar downstairs by the entrance . My favourite hotel in Paris,highly recommended

We had a very particular and individual schedule, which the concierge service and the staff at the Regina was more than capable to handle + providing additional nice surprises that made our weekend very special.

We absolutely loved our stay in the Family Suite at Regina Paris. Our suite was on the top floor with a breathtaking view of the Eiffel Tower. Our daughters stayed in a bunk bed room with its own balcony. There was a TV room with another balcony. Bathroom with huge tiled tub and a balcony with Eiffel Tower views. And a large king bedroom with yet another balcony. This elegant hotel offers twice a day housekeeping with turndown service and fresh water bottles daily. Full breakfast includes a buffet as well as omelettes and pancakes to order. The hotel is easy walking distance to museums, metro stations and the beautiful Tuileries Garden is steps away. You are surrounded by cafes, shopping and attractions with a knowledgeable concierge to help with your plans. I cannot say enough about the friendly staff who made our family feel so comfortable and welcome. We cannot wait to go back.

What an incredible experience, the room and the staff were incredible and surprised my now fiance with a completely decorated bedroom after our special moment. Anytime we are back in Paris we will be staying here. Perfection.

Your staff, our accommodations, and the hotel are exceptional in every way. The detail and care your staff displayed absolutely made my trip to Paris memorable. The gentleman who checked me in and cared for every detail as I was a last-minute lone traveler who had to leave their existing hotel due to construction was amazing and lovely.
I can't thank you enough for making me feel comfortable and doted on. You are a jewel among your peers.

We stayed for 4 nights (family of 4) and we had booked a family room. Luxury atmosphere, very attentive staff at reception and the location of this hotel was perfect for reaching shops and museums. Lovely interior.
The only complaint we have is that housekeeping was absolutely chaotic and not what we expected.. some amenities were not refilled and when we phoned for water it was never brought. the first day the cleaning lady just entered the bathroom when it was occupied.. for a 5 star hotel this is really not up to standard.

The quality of the accommodations, the Parisian ambience, and the convenient location are all exceptional, but what really puts the Hotel Regina Louvre at the top of our list is the staff. Even the kids commented on how incredibly friendly and helpful each and every person was. The Hotel Regina Louvre was an important part of our Paris vacation and exceeded our expectations in every way. If you have a chance to stay here, take it -- you will not be disappointed!

We stayed at this beautiful hotel before the Pandemic and had been due to return in 2020. The hotel kindly honoured our booking and we were so delighted to visit again. On both occasions we stayed in an Eiffel Tower Suite and for us, this provides the most beautiful view in the city. The staff were very busy, but supremely efficient. Nothing was too much trouble. We had booked a late train back to London and the staff accommodated us as the weather was so bad and my husband needed to work. I cant tell you how much I appreciated the small gift left in our room for my birthday. The location is perfect, given proximity to the Louvre and Musee DOrsay as well as some incredible shopping. But for us, the absolute joy of being able to return to a beautiful room after a busy day and watch the Eiffel Tower sparkle on the hour. For us, its perfect. Thank you so much to everyone for taking such great care of us. Couldnt recommend this hotel more highly.

Loved the room, so big and comfortable
Our concierge David helped us plan all off our activities and he is a professional in every way. Best concierge I have ever experienced in any hotel in the world. We will be back.

My husband and I took our two young girls to Paris in the first week of March and stayed in the Hotel Regina. I will note that it also happened to be Fashion week and there were clearly several high end clients staying in the hotel at the same time. I was incredibly impressed by how warm, welcoming and helpful the staff were. They never seemed annoyed by us having small children, in fact they were accommodating beyond our expectations. We stayed in a junior suite, which was huge by comparison to some of my other European travels. The lobby is absolute perfection. From the second you hit the doors to come into the hotel, you can feel the five star experience. Every part of the experience felt luxurious and Parisian. They have done an excellent job preserving the history in this hotel, while updating it to have modern amenities. The other huge plus was the location. I think this may be the best spot to be! The hotel is across the street from the Louvre and is centrally located so that you can walk to most major attractions. We raisiny walked to the Eiffel Tower, Notre Dame, St Chappelle, Sacr Cur, Arc de Triomphe, Champs Elyses and more. Also there are a swath of bistros just a block away. Tiny grocery stores within a few block perimeter. The rue saint honor (French Rodeo drive) is a block away. I felt like this was the perfect hotel no matter the type of strolling you were looking to do. If you are traveling with children, the hotel is also across from the Tularies Gardens, which is just amazing. I really just dont think we could have picked a better hotel, especially given the price point! I highly recommend the Hotel Regina.

Great hotel. Very good service. Going the extra mile absolutely no problem.
Enjoyable breakfast menz and location.
Great Bar to enjoy a drink in quite atmosphere.
In the centrr of Paris directly around the corner of Louvre
Highly recommend.

Excellently located by the louvre and the tuileries with views over most of paris.

Beautifully and traditionally restored rooms.

Excellent restaurant - limited menu but creative and cozy English bat.

Great welcome from Marlene.

Try for an eiffel tower suite.

After visiting Paris for decades and staying from the plaza athenee down and being dissatisfied we have found the answer.

Back for the rugby World Cup!

Outside: a beautiful historic building in an absolutely premium location.

Inside: stunning period decor in the lobby. We stayed in the Eiffel Suite- extremely well appointed with very comfortable bed and period decor. Effective black out curtains. Brilliant soundproofing. The view- well we were in the Eiffel Suite! The only criticism of the room would be the variable intensity of the hot water in the shower-not going to extremes but definitely not a consistent temperature.

Service: Exceptional. From Check In staff helping explain the French Covid Pass procedure, advice to facilitate this in the easiest way, to being escorted to our suite and the staff member (unfortunately I can't remember her name but she speaks Greek as well) taking the time to explain all the room features. Breakfast was included and the Breakfast staff also super polite as well as incredibly efficient.

I spend a lot of time travelling the world in my job, and normally stay in 4* Chains like Hilton, Marriott etc due to employer contracts. This was a special trip for our 15th Wedding Anniversary so we looked 'outside the box' and found the Regina. It is truly the 'Next Level' over the normal 4* fare in both Service and Style. It takes a great deal to impress me but this hotel definitely has that elusive 'Wow' factor. Yes we paid more to stay here but it was most definitely worth it.

If I could give 1 million stars I would! Having visited back in 2017 Ive been desperate to get back & this visit was even more incredible than the last which I didnt think was possible! The staff are the loveliest & they are so kind and welcoming

We have had such a great experience! Everyone so so kind and nice, and the location of the hotel is marvelous. The room was nice, but the view was breath taking.
So many places, colours and the great Parisian atmosphere... we could get all that just from our window. We will definitely return! Linda & comp

Excellent characterful Belle poque hotel with brilliant service and very comfortable probably recently refurbished rooms. Great location. My room overlooked the Louvre and I could see the Eiffel Tower but despite being next a busy road it was completely quiet. The service was in a different league to what Im used to in Paris. Good breakfasts with lots of choice and an attractive looking bar. It all felt welcoming and Representative of the best that Paris can offer.

The hotel was awesome, a fantastic room with a view of the Eifel Tower and soooo comfortable. The Staff was the best I have ever dealt with, from the time I walked into the hotel until we said our goodbyes....they felt like long-time friends. I have never felt so comfortable and welcomed as I did here. They are so professional, friendly, kind and they answered all my questions and provided outstanding dinner recommendations, and even mapped out my list of "Must see" locations.... I would love to give a big shout-0ut to Marlene, Varileke, Lynda, and Marjorie....they are the Best of the Best and every hotel should have them on their staff.

The location is perfect! The staff is wonderful. Concierge personnel are always pleasant, gave great directions, made/changed reservations. Made suggestions, when asked, and they were accurate.
Could single out one or two individuals that worked with, but the entire team is fabulous!!
We plan to stay at Regina on our next trip to Paris - maybe June 2024 - just before Olympics.
Save us a room !!

We stayed a 3 night w/end at the beautiful Hotel Regina next to the Louvre in Feb '22 - the location is very special & many of the important historical places of interest are within walking distance. Jordan gave us the history of the hotel (previously a riding school for the Kings Henri III & IV) over dinner. The hotel decor is classic Parisian with stunning attention to detail. We had a good breakfast & you must order the Classic French Rum Baba which we enjoyed after dinner with a B&B Cocktail.
Our junior suite was amazing & had views of the Eiffel Tower with sunsets every evening.
What absolutely blew us away was the staff and the service. This is a game changer - the attention to detail from every single member of staff was outstanding. It's probably unfair to single out some (as everyone was so fabulous) however, Marjorie, Linda, Clment & all of the Concierge Team deserve a special mention. They are available 24/7 - the service, advice, recommendations, reservations etc was spectacular. Also, Giselle from Room Service was so lovely, friendly and attentive. The porter, Abdoulaye was brilliant too.
We have stayed in some great locations worldwide, what sets this hotel apart is the Staff. The service, warmth and friendliness of every staff member from the moment we confirmed the reservation to the time we checked out was was so fantastic.
We have been to Paris many times, our return visit will certainly include the Hotel Regina. Merci  tous!
